h Friday from 0800   1630  and evenings Monday through Thursday from 1900   2200  Reference librarians can also teach all of our patrons to use the print and electronic resources available at Preston Library  Librarians help develop search strategies that empower library users to find needed information  Librarians are also available for personal research consultations to assist our cadets and faculty with their ongoing research projects  To schedule an individual consultation please contact the Reference Desk  Instruction Library orientations and bibliographic instruction are available for any VMI class to help cadets take full advantage of the ever expanding and improving resources available  Librarians identify appropriate resources  describe their scope  demonstrate the mechanics of their use  explain useful search strategies  and provide evaluation guidelines  Instruction sessions cover an unlimited range of levels  including tours and orientations given to those participating in the Summer Transition Program  STP  and to new cadets  instruction in basic research materials and methods for introductory courses  and in depth instruction on specialized resources for upper level courses  Instruction is often designed to meet the specific needs of the class  Faculty members may arrange for library instruction by contacting Col Janet Holly or Maj  Accacia Mullen at ReferenceDesk vmi edu  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissi